      • setValue

        public int setValue(java.util.GregorianCalendar g,
                    java.lang.String val,
                    int nsamp)
        Used to append a value to the column data arrays and returns an int to be sent to edge.
        Parameters:
        g - The GregorianCalendar from CampbellParser that stores data/time associated with data value

        Returns:

      • setValue

        public int setValue(java.util.GregorianCalendar g,
                    java.lang.String val1,
                    java.lang.String val2,
                    int nsamp)
        Used to append a value to a derived column data array.
        Parameters:
        g - The GregorianCalendar from CampbellParser that stores date/time associated with data values
        val1 - First value coming from the primary column. Must reference a column with an instrument that has derived configuration.
        val2 - Second value coming from the secondary column.
        nsamp - Sample index.
        Returns:
        Integer value to be sent to edge.
